      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOLAR SPECTRUM (1) has missed the frame at his last couple of starts but just a few runs back broke the clock when winning over 350m at this track, taking a NG in a dominant 19.78. Can measure up again if runs up to recent best times. CANYA HANDLE IT (2) flew the lids with a sensational early split and hit the frame with a 5 length third (30.48) over 527m at Gunnedah. Form from his last run is proving very strong. Can feature again. PIRATE RIOT (3) is having his first start around this circuit. In the money last start when third (29.83) at The Gardens over 515m. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Expected to feature. RED ROCK RAZZLE (7) is always hard to beat when he races at this trip.",
